column1: The table shows the overall properties of the defined orphans (extracted from Table S1) and the potentially functions assigned to categories in COGs, MultiFun and GO with predicted probability scores of the 1,431 orphans. For each of the three function classification schema COGs, MultiFun and GO, the functional assignments to a given orphan are based on: (1) All functions with predicted probability>=0.8 are assigned to the orphans;  (2) if no functions in a given function classification scheme (e.g. COGs, MultiFun,GO) have predicted probability>=0.8, we assign the function with maximum predicted probability in the function classification scheme to the orphan.
